Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.49,0:00:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so happy you can join us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.56,0:00:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for this month’s program.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.16,0:00:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m here with my good friend
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.96,0:00:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and cohost, Leon Weaver.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.56,0:00:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.43,0:00:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Leon, welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.03,0:00:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,David, I’m delighted to be here with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.27,0:00:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I’d like to tell you\Na little something about Leon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.20,0:00:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was invited into Bethel in 1990,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.71,0:00:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was assigned to the Service Department
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.38,0:00:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and Leon was one of the overseers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.11,0:00:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the Service Department,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,at times we had to deal\Nwith some very difficult matters
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes you needed advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.42,0:00:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could always rely\Non Leon to help me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.69,0:00:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d go into his office,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.39,0:00:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,he’d set aside whatever it was\Nhe was working on,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.99,0:00:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,he’d listen, and then he’d give his input.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.86,0:00:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciated the experience\NI acquired in the Service Department,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.97,0:00:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and Leon was certainly part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.70,0:00:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is one reason why I have love
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.14,0:01:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and respect for that brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.84,0:01:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Leon, what can we look forward to\Nin this month’s program?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.01,0:01:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.78,0:01:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth gave up a prestigious career
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.75,0:01:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to do more for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.76,0:01:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How did her decision
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.99,0:01:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,change the course of her life?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.69,0:01:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll debut a fascinating new series.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.20,0:01:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It will reveal aspects\Nof our theocratic history
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.03,0:01:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you may not be familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.90,0:01:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.27,0:01:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.81,0:01:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting® for November 2021.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.87,0:01:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Through his prophet Isaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.63,0:02:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah made a wonderful promise,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.17,0:02:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,one that’s being fulfilled today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.34,0:02:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We can read about it at Isaiah 60:17:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.34,0:02:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“Instead of the copper I will bring in gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“and instead of the iron\NI will bring in silver,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“instead of the wood, copper,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.59,0:02:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“and instead of the stones, iron;
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.19,0:02:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I will appoint peace as your overseers
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.63,0:02:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and righteousness as your task assigners.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.70,0:02:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, this reference to “overseers”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.43,0:02:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and “task assigners”\N—that sounds like organization, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.70,0:02:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is Jehovah telling us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s saying that we can expect
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to see organizational arrangements\Ngetting better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.88,0:02:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you’ve been associated\Nwith the truth for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.55,0:02:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you’ll agree that Isaiah’s prophecy\Nis being fulfilled today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.22,0:02:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So for this broadcast,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.29,0:02:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we’d review\Nsome of the improvements
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.63,0:02:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve seen just since World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.49,0:03:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the period\Nmost of us are familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.63,0:03:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some of you will be hearing\Nabout these things for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.47,0:03:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Others will have lived through it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.37,0:03:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and for them it’ll bring back fond memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s go back.\NIt’ll be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.58,0:03:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I call this part\N“Do You Remember When . . . ?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Before World War II\Nand for a number of years after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.09,0:03:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,many congregations\Ndidn’t have a Kingdom Hall of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.72,0:03:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They were actually encouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet in private homes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.20,0:03:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or in rented facilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The thinking was that if you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.73,0:03:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,were in a rented facility or a private home,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.24,0:03:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you had more flexibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.47,0:03:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You could move the meeting place
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.31,0:03:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from one place to the other very easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were problems; there were drawbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.14,0:03:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the space
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.75,0:03:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,would be shared with other organizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you couldn’t leave your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,literature, magazines,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,speaker’s stand, and maybe even a sound system
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.05,0:03:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hall at the end of the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When the meeting was over,\Nyou’d have to pack it all up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.03,0:04:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.86,0:04:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.03,0:04:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you had to arrive very early\Nand clean the place up 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.63,0:04:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,after a particularly rowdy group\Nof people had used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.17,0:04:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there were cigar smokers\Nin that group, you were in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.11,0:04:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very difficult to air the place out\Nin time for the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.91,0:04:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, remember, in those days,\Npeople could smoke in a private hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.82,0:04:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you could smoke in an airplane\N—they could smoke almost anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.32,0:04:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So this was a real problem for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There were other problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.86,0:04:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we had a Kingdom Hall in my hometown,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.90,0:04:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the congregation met in a rented facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in October,\Nthe place was decorated for Halloween,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.00,0:04:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and in December, there was\Na great big Christmas tree on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn’t move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.24,0:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this was in Canada,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:04:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and portraits\Nof the King and Queen of England
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.51,0:05:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the British flag\Nwere permanent fixtures in the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.58,0:05:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn’t remove\Nany of it for the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, to their credit,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,many interested persons\Nattended our meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.69,0:05:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And to them, it wasn’t\Nthe meeting place that was important;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.10,0:05:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it was what\Nthey were learning there that counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.33,0:05:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of our meeting places,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,at first, congregations were on their own
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.74,0:05:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,when it came to building them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.77,0:05:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at times, the most a congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.54,0:05:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,could afford was to purchase the land,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.41,0:05:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes that land would sit there
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.28,0:05:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for years because it would
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.05,0:05:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,take years to get the money together
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.02,0:05:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to build the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.62,0:05:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then once they had the money together,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.46,0:05:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,were there enough brothers who could take
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.56,0:05:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the lead in the construction?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes on a weekend, you’d see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.16,0:05:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,just one or two brothers working away
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.03,0:05:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,at the site of the new hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.73,0:05:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to love them for their perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.74,0:05:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,our Kingdom Hall construction\Nis supervised by the LDCs,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.31,0:06:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,with lots of qualified volunteers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and practical Kingdom Halls\Ncan be constructed in a short period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.75,0:06:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the meetings?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.75,0:06:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For years, the Theocratic Ministry School,\NService Meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Congregation Book Study,\Nand {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Watchtower{
} Study
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.62,0:06:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,were all about an hour in length.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.63,0:06:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So were the public talks
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.93,0:06:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—when we had them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.93,0:06:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at first, a public talk\Nwasn’t scheduled every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.60,0:06:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There’d be a series of four or eight talks,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.67,0:06:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if you could schedule that many speakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, for a while,\Nthe congregation wouldn’t have a public talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.18,0:06:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.55,0:06:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the Theocratic Ministry School
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.05,0:06:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t get under way until 1943,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.68,0:06:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and it took time for the brothers to develop
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the skills to deliver an hour talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But in time, they were delivering
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.69,0:06:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,excellent public talks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.83,0:06:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.23,0:06:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when we had individual handbills
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for each public talk
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.83,0:06:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,with the name of the speaker printed on them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.50,0:07:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Until 1959,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.51,0:07:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,only brothers were enrolled in the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.54,0:07:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For some years, during the first few minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.84,0:07:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the school there was a roll call,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.35,0:07:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the names of all the brothers\Nenrolled in the school were read out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.65,0:07:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when your name was read out,\Nyou were to answer, “Present.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.19,0:07:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A few rebels would say, “Here.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.19,0:07:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were supposed to say, “Present.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.53,0:07:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, initially,\Naccording to the instructions,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.60,0:07:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,if anyone was deliberately
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.60,0:07:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and habitually absent over a period of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.70,0:07:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,he was dropped from the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, that was discontinued.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.91,0:07:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the roll-call arrangement\Ngot me into a bit of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.08,0:07:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in our congregation\Nwhen the roll was being called each week,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.78,0:07:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed that there\Nwere a few young brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.95,0:07:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who were just a little bit older than I was\Nwho would answer, “Present.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.12,0:07:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So one night after the school,\NI asked the school servant
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,if I could have my name read out\Nat the next meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.79,0:07:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He warmly commended me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.93,0:08:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And sure enough,\NI got my name read out the following week.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.63,0:08:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone congratulated me after the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t understand why.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.44,0:08:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I only said, “Present.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.47,0:08:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem was that I didn’t know\Nthat when you got your name read out,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.81,0:08:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you were agreeing to give a talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.95,0:08:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I was just signing up\Nto have my name read out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a couple of months later,\Non April 8, 1953,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.39,0:08:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I delivered my first\Neight-minute talk on the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.93,0:08:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“Proclaiming the World’s Doom.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why an eight-minute talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.66,0:08:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we didn’t have Bible readings yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you were on the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.83,0:08:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you were giving an eight-minute talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.64,0:08:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today, we make sure\Neveryone understands what’s involved
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.11,0:08:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in being a student in the midweek meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.94,0:08:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.91,0:08:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we received the {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}New World Translation 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}of the Christian Greek Scriptures{
} in English,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were encouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring it to the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:09:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the Hebrew Scriptures,\Nyou would have the {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}American Standard Version 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.62,0:09:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or the {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}King James Version 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.29,0:09:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}—mo{
}stly the Am{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}erican Standard Version 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.23,0:09:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because it had Jehovah’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So you’d have two Bibles\Nto bring to the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.60,0:09:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s the one for the Hebrew Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}New World Translation{
}\Nfor the Greek Scriptures—two Bibles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.50,0:09:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.84,0:09:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But later, the {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}New World Translation {
}\N{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}of the Hebrew Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.38,0:09:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was released in installments.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.88,0:09:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you’d get a volume every year or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.38,0:09:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we received each new volume,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.78,0:09:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we were encouraged\Nto bring it to the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.59,0:09:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in time, those volumes\Nstarted to pile up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.46,0:09:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so that by 1960,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.76,0:09:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you might have volumes 1 through 5\Nof the Hebrew Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,also the Greek Scriptures,\Nand your regular study aids!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had thick study aids in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We had big briefcases\Nand strong backs in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We were really happy to get\Nthe complete {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}New World Translation 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.08,0:09:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in just one volume in 1961.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.82,0:10:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s say a word about music.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s something that’s near\Nand dear to my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.02,0:10:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,For many years,\Nit was left up to the local servants
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to decide which songs the congregation\Nwould sing at the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.59,0:10:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the chairman of a particular meeting\Nwould select the songs,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.26,0:10:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but his choice wasn’t always final.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.33,0:10:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Many Kingdom Halls had a piano
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,or some other instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.24,0:10:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to accompany the singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.57,0:10:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But often the musician couldn’t play\Nall of the songs in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so we’d have to sing the songs he could play.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.68,0:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We got to know those few songs really well!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But those humble musicians\Ndid their best to accompany our singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.22,0:10:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as a result of all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.22,0:10:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the words to those songs\Nwe sang nearly 70 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.99,0:10:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,still come readily to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.80,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the written review?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you don’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.47,0:10:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Congregations periodically
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.64,0:10:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,had a written review of material\Nthat had been covered
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.41,0:11:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Theocratic Ministry School\Nover the previous weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we had a half hour to answer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,about 25 questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.38,0:11:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, when the half hour was up,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we would write our name on the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.15,0:11:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,hand it in to the school servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.12,0:11:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would take\Nall the papers home to grade them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.43,0:11:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if there were 25 questions,\Nyou’d get 4 points apiece
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.26,0:11:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for each correct answer—100 points total.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.47,0:11:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a week later,\Nhe’d return the papers to us at the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.97,0:11:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the early years of the arrangement\N(I remember well),
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.81,0:11:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,he’d announce the highest\Nand lowest grade to the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.31,0:11:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, thankfully, he didn’t mention the names
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the one who got\Nthe highest and lowest score.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.32,0:11:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, later, that arrangement to announce
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.39,0:11:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest and lowest grade\Nwas discontinued.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.19,0:11:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember when circuit assemblies
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.02,0:11:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,began on Friday evening
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.16,0:11:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and continued through Sunday afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.36,0:11:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A full program
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.86,0:11:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was presented Saturday afternoon and evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.90,0:12:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There was never a dull moment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.17,0:12:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,on Saturday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.60,0:12:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There were lively demonstrations
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.21,0:12:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that kept our interest
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.57,0:12:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,right up to the end of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.84,0:12:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the sets were very elaborate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nsuppose a publisher was demonstrating
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.95,0:12:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a presentation from door to door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.95,0:12:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, today\Nwe’d just imagine there was a door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.56,0:12:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But back then at the circuit assembly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.46,0:12:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there might be a frame\Nwith a painted door on the stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.23,0:12:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe even a doorbell\Nfor the publisher to ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if the householder\Nwas supposed to be interested,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.94,0:12:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you knew it\Nbecause the house number was 777.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.14,0:12:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the householder\Nwas going to be opposed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.44,0:12:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you knew that as well\Nbecause the house number would be 666.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, on one program that I remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.75,0:12:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the publisher knocks on the door\Nand a brother dressed as a priest answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:12:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He puts up a real argument about the Trinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.66,0:12:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about visual aids
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.89,0:13:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,—but you never forgot what you saw and heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.03,0:13:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you remember when\Neach congregation had a congregation servant
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.34,0:13:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and up to seven other servants:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.64,0:13:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the assistant congregation servant,\Nthe Bible study servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the accounts servant,\Nthe {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Watchtower{
} study servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.25,0:13:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the magazine-territory servant,\Nthe literature servant, 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.55,0:13:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Theocratic Ministry School servant?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.62,0:13:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at that time,\Napart from book study conductors,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.92,0:13:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn’t have more than\Neight servants in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.73,0:13:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So unless someone moved,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.50,0:13:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a young man had no chance\Nof becoming a servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.17,0:13:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So how could a young man\Nreach out for more responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.44,0:13:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And how would the prophecy recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.57,0:13:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at Micah 5:5 ever be fulfilled?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.08,0:13:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There Jehovah promised:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.08,0:13:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“We will raise up against him\Nseven shepherds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.45,0:13:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, eight princes of mankind.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.05,0:13:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, seven represents completeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.79,0:14:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So eight princes—that would indicate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.42,0:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that there would be\Nmore than enough men in the congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.33,0:14:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide theocratic direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.40,0:14:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But how could that be\Nwhen there was basically
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.23,0:14:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a limit of eight servants per congregation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.17,0:14:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer came in 1971.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.74,0:14:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We were thrilled when we understood
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.77,0:14:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that each congregation has a body of elders,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.81,0:14:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is no set number\Nof elders or ministerial servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.55,0:14:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As many as are qualified can be appointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.49,0:14:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when I was baptized 66 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.72,0:14:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn’t have to be approved\Nfor baptism by the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.83,0:14:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The only questions asked\Nof baptism candidates
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.06,0:14:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,were the two they answered\Nat the conclusion of the baptism talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.30,0:14:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That led to a few strange situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.34,0:14:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,On a few occasions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.17,0:14:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—much to the surprise of the servants—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,someone would rush up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.01,0:14:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to the front of the hall at the end
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.25,0:14:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of the baptism talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.45,0:14:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,answer the two questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.82,0:15:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and get baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Something more was needed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.69,0:15:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—assurance that the individual\Nreally knew what he was doing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.22,0:15:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially that he was living\Nin harmony with Scriptural principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.53,0:15:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So in 1967,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.40,0:15:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,questions were provided\Nso that the responsible brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.00,0:15:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,could be assured that each candidate\Nwas truly qualified for baptism.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.51,0:15:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Those questions have been refined\Nover the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, we go over some 60 questions
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.28,0:15:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with baptism candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.35,0:15:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The copper has turned to gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember when there were
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.79,0:15:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,very few pictures in our publications?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.66,0:15:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the few that we had
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.99,0:15:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,were usually in black and white
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.49,0:15:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,or only two colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.66,0:15:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, our spiritual food
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.83,0:15:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is served in attractive publications
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.20,0:15:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in full color.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, those of us who’ve served
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.21,0:15:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in foreign-language congregations\Nwill also remember
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.97,0:16:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when a new publication in English
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.98,0:16:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,might not be available\Nin another language for several years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.65,0:16:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Study articles trailed by several months.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.35,0:16:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s before it became possible\Nfor the branches
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.09,0:16:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to do simultaneous printing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So here’s how it worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.96,0:16:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Material in English\Nwould be mailed to the branches
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.29,0:16:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,by regular mail for translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.86,0:16:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If the translators had a question\Nabout the meaning of a sentence in English,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.80,0:16:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they would use regular mail\Nto send their question to headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, headquarters would answer back\Nby regular mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.58,0:16:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This back and forth\N—it could take quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.75,0:16:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And in some countries, mail service was poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.15,0:16:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, today,\Nthanks to special computer programs
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.62,0:16:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that our brothers have developed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.72,0:16:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ability to communicate electronically
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and some other factors, we’re able to release
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.16,0:16:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,most language editions simultaneously\Nwith the English.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.10,0:16:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What an improvement!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, speaking of our literature,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,do you realize that it’s been some 31 years
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.08,0:17:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,since the decision was made\Nthat in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.14,0:17:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d no longer ask\Nfor a contribution for our literature?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.58,0:17:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, the arrangement\Nwas extended worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.19,0:17:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s been a real blessing for our brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were asking\Nfor contributions for literature,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,some brothers in Africa and other places
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.53,0:17:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn’t afford to have a Wa{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}tchtower \Nf{
}or every member of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.20,0:17:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They were just too poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.47,0:17:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about bound books?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.24,0:17:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll tell you an experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.24,0:17:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In one African country, a missionary noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.18,0:17:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that a young brother quoted\Na wide variety of scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in his comments, and he got curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, he asked the young brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“How did you come to know\Nso many scriptures?”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.96,0:17:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The brother replied:\N“It’s the Reas{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}oning boo{
}k.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.93,0:18:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I read it every chance I get.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The missionary asked him, “What do you mean
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.60,0:18:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you read it every chance you get?”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he replied:\N“I don’t have a Reas{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}oning bo{
}ok myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.77,0:18:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“I could never afford one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.71,0:18:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“But I know a sister who has one,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.91,0:18:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“and she lets me borrow it from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.78,0:18:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I read it every chance I get.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.48,0:18:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.75,0:18:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the missionary went out\Nand bought him a {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Reasoning {
} book
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.39,0:18:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and a {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}New World Translation {
}\Nfor good measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.49,0:18:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a great investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.06,0:18:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The young brother\Nwas later called into Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.56,0:18:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and where do you think he was assigned?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.77,0:18:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,To the literature department.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.13,0:18:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers knew\Nthat he appreciated the literature so much
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.17,0:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that he’d make sure the congregations\Nhad the literature they needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.31,0:18:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, looking back,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.38,0:18:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see that the arrangements\Nback then served a purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They were like fine copper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:19:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not look down on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.46,0:19:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, we take the view expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.89,0:19:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,at Zechariah 4:10:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.13,0:19:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who has despised the day
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.60,0:19:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of small beginnings?”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.90,0:19:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as those taking the lead\Nsaw a better way of doing things,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.84,0:19:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn’t hesitate to make adjustments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.44,0:19:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s very faith-strengthening.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.94,0:19:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best is yet to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.81,0:19:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned in the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.82,0:19:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this may be the first time that some of you\Nhave heard about these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.42,0:19:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not ask someone\Nwho has been in the truth for many years
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what it was like\Nwhen he was new in the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That could lead\Nto a very stimulating discussion!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.73,0:19:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.13,0:19:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for those historical insights, David.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.34,0:19:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,how much has changed just in our lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.14,0:19:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you really see how Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.74,0:19:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,keeps improving his organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.25,0:20:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have a great example
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.58,0:20:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of someone who has seen all of the changes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.65,0:20:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve talked about and more: John Mills.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.42,0:20:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see how he\Nhas faithfully served Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.63,0:20:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,through multiple assignments and challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.90,0:20:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised with three sisters,\Nand my mom was in the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.01,0:20:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember sitting on the sofa
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.01,0:20:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and just talking about spiritual things\Nwith my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.72,0:20:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And she taught us to appreciate\Nany assignment that we had
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.52,0:20:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—to see it as something very special.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pioneering was my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.33,0:20:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilead to me was a way to give to others
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.83,0:20:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be very busy in service.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.24,0:20:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “I really want to go to Gilead
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.64,0:21:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but, if it’s possible, to have a wife too.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.51,0:21:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just thought, ‘Boy, are you pushy!’
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.35,0:21:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, and so—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.22,0:21:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah gave me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.85,0:21:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.82,0:21:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And to my amazement,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.53,0:21:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there was the most lovely, spiritual sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.37,0:21:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a student in the same class, Lois.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.17,0:21:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I met her and was able to marry her
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.84,0:21:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one week after Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.18,0:21:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Arriving as a newlywed couple
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.65,0:21:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in a missionary home with seven other people
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.52,0:21:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,was quite daunting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.25,0:21:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But we didn’t let that faze us;\Nwe were on our honeymoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.39,0:21:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Colombia was a paradise spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.59,0:21:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We loved it so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.60,0:21:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the kind of life we wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.37,0:22:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lois was a great teacher in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.61,0:22:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I always enjoyed working with her;\Nshe was actually a great support for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.11,0:22:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, Colombia had its risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.88,0:22:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember in the mornings,\Nsometimes it got to the point when
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.45,0:22:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I would look at Lois and she would look\Nat me and we’d just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.79,0:22:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“If I don’t see you, see you\Nin the Paradise,” you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.10,0:22:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Colombia became our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.40,0:22:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We traveled the length and breadth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.57,0:22:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the country\Nin our different assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.77,0:22:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We had been over 20 years in Colombia\Nwhen it became very evident
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.74,0:22:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that Lois’s mom would need our care.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.31,0:22:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This, of course,\Nwould mean leaving our assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.22,0:22:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It almost tore my heart apart\Nto leave Colombia.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.99,0:23:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt I was abandoning so many privileges
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.60,0:23:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and my treasured assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.10,0:23:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In the U.S.A.,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.10,0:23:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we were working as a team,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.27,0:23:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could see Lois really organized,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.24,0:23:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,making the best of the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.01,0:23:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping her mom
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,was really the source,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.62,0:23:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way, of her deep joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.16,0:23:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping others was just a way of life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.26,0:23:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to Lois.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.33,0:23:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t matter what privilege you have
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.70,0:23:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and what responsibility;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.97,0:23:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,true happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.51,0:23:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is always found in giving.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.28,0:23:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, Lois got very ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.05,0:23:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lois never cried about her illness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.85,0:23:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,or felt sorry for herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.95,0:23:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She always was focused on others
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.05,0:24:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and would give of herself, even 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.99,0:24:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,within the pain of illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.06,0:24:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that Lois has passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.90,0:24:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,many times I think of her example,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.17,0:24:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just motivates me to carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.78,0:24:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here at the Central America branch
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.08,0:24:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I am surrounded by such a loving family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.62,0:24:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I resolved when
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.42,0:24:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through this situation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.76,0:24:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with losing my wife to find others
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.36,0:24:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that were in similar situations
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.60,0:24:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe sit down for a coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.90,0:24:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Just that fellow feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.07,0:24:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of just being able
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.54,0:24:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to show interest and to encourage
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.44,0:24:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,another person is a great joy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.75,0:25:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that I personally find one\Nof the most helpful things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.59,0:25:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to endure trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.52,0:25:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,John’s life of faithful service reminds me
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.53,0:25:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth found at 2 Corinthians 1:3, 4:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.53,0:25:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“[Jehovah] comforts us in all our trials
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.01,0:25:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that we may be able to comfort others
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.78,0:25:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“in any sort of trial with the comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.05,0:25:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that we receive from God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.52,0:25:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever wondered
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.29,0:25:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,why we sing at our meetings?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.72,0:25:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or why we attend conventions,\Nusually in the summer?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.16,0:25:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Many who are young in years\Nor new in the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.03,0:25:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,may not be familiar\Nwith certain aspects of our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.31,0:26:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, this rich spiritual history
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.31,0:26:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is your heritage,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.81,0:26:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want you to become acquainted with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.02,0:26:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.09,0:26:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,has approved the development of a new series: 
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.02,0:26:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Our History in Motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.96,0:26:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each segment will look at an aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.36,0:26:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of our worship through time,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.13,0:26:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,similar to what David shared with us earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.57,0:26:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The series will help us see
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.07,0:26:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that our worship is rooted,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.84,0:26:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not in tradition or custom,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.31,0:26:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the truth found in God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.02,0:26:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for our first episode,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.19,0:26:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks at the history\Nof singing praises to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.40,0:26:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was made in secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.90,0:26:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden in the lining of a jacket,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.64,0:27:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then smuggled out of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.10,0:27:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.11,0:27:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A recording\Nof brothers and sisters in Siberia
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.61,0:27:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,singing Kingdom songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.45,0:27:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent it from one side\Nof the earth to the other 
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.82,0:27:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to be played at the 1958\Ninternational convention in New York
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.82,0:27:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for an audience of more than 250,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.49,0:27:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is singing so important\Nto Jehovah’s Witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.37,0:27:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s find out in this episode\Nof Ou{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}r History in Motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.71,0:27:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s worshippers
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.72,0:27:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,have long praised him with song.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.29,0:27:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did singing become
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.52,0:27:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a part of our modern-day worship?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.02,0:27:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The story begins more than 150 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.66,0:28:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The year is about 1869
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.56,0:28:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in Allegheny, Pennsylvania, U.S.A.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.07,0:28:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles Taze Russell
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.07,0:28:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is a young man\Nsearching for Scriptural truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.74,0:28:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One evening he’s walking along\Nand hears something
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.08,0:28:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—singing coming from a religious meeting\Nbeing held in a basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.75,0:28:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes in, and what he hears sparks a fire
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.05,0:28:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for Bible study like never before.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.19,0:28:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, Russell and his associates
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.16,0:28:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,make music’s role in pure worship clear
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.40,0:28:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,as they rediscover Bible truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.73,0:28:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles Taze Russell
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.87,0:28:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,may have come to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.04,0:28:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how the power of music can stir emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.11,0:28:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,from a music business\Nthat his father owned for a period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.91,0:28:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He believed that “the singing of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.55,0:28:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“is a good way to get it into the heads
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.72,0:28:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and hearts of God’s people.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.46,0:29:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The first issue of {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Zion’s Watch Tower,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.56,0:29:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,published in July of 1879,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.53,0:29:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,announced a songbook
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.53,0:29:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—the first of many to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.10,0:29:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Songs of the Bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.64,0:29:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It contained 144 hymns,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.41,0:29:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or religious songs of praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.07,0:29:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible Students sang\Nat their meetings and assemblies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.11,0:29:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it like to sing\Nthese songs back in the early 1900’s?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.15,0:29:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that you’re\Nat one of Charles Taze Russell’s lectures. 
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.89,0:29:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk in,\Nyou’re handed a small sheet of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.26,0:29:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You look for a seat, but it’s packed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.26,0:29:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As the crowd quiets down,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.67,0:29:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they announce that the meeting\Nwill start with a song and prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.17,0:29:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In a church,\Nyou expect to find a hymn book in your pew,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.17,0:29:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but this is a rented hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.64,0:29:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you realize\Nthat the paper you were handed
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.91,0:29:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,has the song lyrics,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.95,0:30:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and it also has a place\Nto leave your name and address
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.69,0:30:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,if you’d like a Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.99,0:30:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the audience\Nstarts to sing, you join in.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.76,0:30:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What did songs sound like back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.16,0:30:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s listen to a song\Nwe sang for over eight decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.10,0:30:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a recording from 1916.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.88,0:30:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a little different than how
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.95,0:30:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,our songs sound today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.98,0:30:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Compare different versions of this song,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.38,0:30:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll notice that the lyrics
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.39,0:30:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and theme changed over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.02,0:30:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a version of “All Hail”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.66,0:30:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Watch Tower Male Quartet in 1935.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.37,0:31:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In our first songbook this song was called
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.08,0:31:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“All Hail the Power of Jesus’ Name,”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.85,0:31:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,which was about, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.85,0:31:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of Jesus’ name
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.88,0:31:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with zero mention of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.39,0:31:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, many songs prior to this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.36,0:31:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,were adapted from existing church hymns.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.93,0:31:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here’s the same song in 1950.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.36,0:31:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of the lyrics
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.16,0:31:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,overemphasizing Jesus’ name,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.57,0:31:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the lyrics refer to “making known God’s will”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.50,0:31:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and mention Jehovah by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.91,0:31:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why all the changes?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.38,0:31:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because our songs reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.88,0:31:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,our current understanding\Nof Scriptural truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.42,0:31:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As the light gets brighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.42,0:31:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we understand the truth more clearly,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.96,0:31:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so the songs change.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.90,0:31:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first songbook explained
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.76,0:31:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,explained the goal to publish 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.47,0:32:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“songs free from objectionable theology,”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.74,0:32:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s been the case ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.04,0:32:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t hold on to songs
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.74,0:32:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for tradition or nostalgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.48,0:32:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We sing them because it’s the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.22,0:32:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,From the 1928 songbook onward,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.22,0:32:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a big shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.25,0:32:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Many songs were written\Nby our brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.66,0:32:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They put more emphasis on Jehovah’s name,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.40,0:32:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,his attributes, and his Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.10,0:32:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can even tell by the title 
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.33,0:32:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Songs of Praise to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.47,0:32:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the songs might even sound familiar,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.74,0:32:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.19,0:32:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Are your parents in the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.19,0:32:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your grandparents?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.76,0:32:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,even your great-grandparents?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.86,0:33:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, they sang the same song as you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.03,0:33:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,at their meetings and assemblies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.93,0:33:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a real legacy!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.14,0:33:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s fast-forward to the 1940’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.84,0:33:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of our brothers\Nwere imprisoned for their faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.54,0:33:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The world was at war and needed good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.01,0:33:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So we intensified
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.01,0:33:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,our preaching and teaching work.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.05,0:33:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is when\Nthe Watchtower Bible School of Gilead
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.82,0:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Theocratic Ministry School started,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.36,0:33:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s also when\Nsinging was reintroduced at our meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.83,0:33:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.86,0:33:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Reintroduced?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.87,0:33:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we stopped singing at meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.50,0:33:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.14,0:33:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Find out in the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.84,0:33:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Our History in Motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.49,0:34:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s a cliff-hanger!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.99,0:34:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.02,0:34:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,why we stopped singing for a time?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.56,0:34:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll want to watch\Nthe second part of this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.60,0:34:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be posted soon on jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.50,0:34:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And look for future episodes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.87,0:34:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Our History in Motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.24,0:34:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.28,0:34:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Awake!{
} magazine
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.28,0:34:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,published the story of Elizabeth Balnave.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.59,0:34:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth explains
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.26,0:34:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,why she made a major career decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.56,0:34:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that decision affect her life?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.43,0:34:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s find out in this episode
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.90,0:34:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of {\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Where Are They Now? 
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.04,0:34:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,As a child, I dreamed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.74,0:34:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of becoming a ballerina.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.75,0:35:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I trained as a ballet dancer from childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.75,0:35:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was taught to give complete obedience\Nto the artistic director,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.75,0:35:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute loyalty to the dance company,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.29,0:35:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and to put ballet before everything else\Nin my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.66,0:35:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally realized there’s no way\Nto get ahead in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.57,0:35:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,without compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.24,0:35:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It just can’t be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.24,0:35:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a life is empty and unsatisfying.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.51,0:35:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is, once you get into that,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.52,0:35:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you get lulled in by that glamour and glitz.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.35,0:35:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, down the road\Nwhen you finally see the trap
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.16,0:35:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you got into,\Nit’s very hard to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.49,0:35:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always tell young people, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.43,0:35:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that it doesn’t matter how good everything\Nseems; it doesn’t matter how great.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.13,0:35:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s always a string attached—always.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.27,0:35:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one day,\Nyou’re going to wake up and it’s a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.91,0:36:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can’t cut a rope that easily
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.18,0:36:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,—meaning you can’t get out of the situation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.38,0:36:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,once Satan has you trapped in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.42,0:36:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And it happens without you even realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.69,0:36:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ballet is discipline,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.32,0:36:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had to figure out a way
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.92,0:36:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to take that skill
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.39,0:36:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and transfer it into my everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.33,0:36:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It took some time,\Nbut I finally figured it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.56,0:36:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s not a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.83,0:36:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.73,0:36:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I had to learn\Nwas to get out of my comfort zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.21,0:36:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We were in Bethel until 1987.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.54,0:36:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack had a job lined up when we left Bethel,\Nand that was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.98,0:36:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t get a job\Nbecause of my physical health issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.42,0:36:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably was in bed for about five months.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.49,0:36:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I started feeling better,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.42,0:36:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s when I realized\Nhow bad the medical bills were getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.13,0:36:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I just dragged myself out of bed\Nand went and looked for a part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.60,0:37:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, through all of this,\NJack and I just kept praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.00,0:37:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew Jehovah would take care of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.77,0:37:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No question about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.71,0:37:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, I did get a job at a law firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.51,0:37:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.84,0:37:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually lasted there 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.15,0:37:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely Jehovah blessed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.65,0:37:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I believe what he was blessing\Nwere my efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.69,0:37:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t quit, and I refused to compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.09,0:37:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When I started seeing\Nthat I was really learning this new skill
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.29,0:37:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was getting good at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.13,0:37:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s when I sat down and I said:\N“Well, Jehovah, I have this new skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.47,0:37:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be able to use it for you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.53,0:37:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing led to another, and I became
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.70,0:37:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,a commuter Bethelite\Nfor the Legal Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.54,0:37:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d say that about 11 years\Nafter I had left Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.64,0:37:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was working and all of a sudden,\NI got sick again with the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.78,0:37:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—complete rapid loss of weight\Nand all the weakness came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.42,0:37:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was eventually diagnosed\Nas having celiac disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.22,0:37:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So once I changed my diet,\NI just started getting better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.66,0:38:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I stayed with the law firm until 2014,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.43,0:38:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and then my husband and I retired\Nand moved to another part of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.43,0:38:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, currently,\NI’m a remote Bethel consultant.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.00,0:38:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you slave for the world,\Nyou really are a slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.67,0:38:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you slave for Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.67,0:38:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in my opinion, you’re not slaving at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.61,0:38:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn’t have a better partnership
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.48,0:38:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,than you and Jehovah,\Nand that’s how I view it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.68,0:38:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re never going to experience\NJehovah to the full
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.12,0:38:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you put yourself out there\Nfor him to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.19,0:38:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had a wonderful life
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.03,0:38:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of extraordinary spiritual privileges.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.56,0:38:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no career in the world\Nthat is ever going to come close to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.24,0:38:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t you say that resilience
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.31,0:38:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the qualities\Nthat has helped Elizabeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.82,0:38:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What can each of us do
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.49,0:39:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to be more resilient?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.86,0:39:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice three practical suggestions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.76,0:39:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in this morning worship presented\Nby Brother Gajus Glockentin.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.10,0:39:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary kept listening to what Jesus was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.77,0:39:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How commendable!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.61,0:39:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She set the right priorities
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.77,0:39:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and is a good example for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.21,0:39:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Martha, her sister, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.55,0:39:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,received loving correction from Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.78,0:39:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as our printed comment puts it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.48,0:39:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let us, today, put ourselves\Nin the shoes of Martha for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.49,0:39:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She showed great interest in supporting Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.59,0:39:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,by providing him a base during his ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.36,0:39:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the difficult area of Judea.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.87,0:39:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.87,0:39:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary and Martha\Nwere probably working together
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.07,0:39:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare things for Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.41,0:39:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But after Jesus arrived,\NMary stopped helping as our text indicates.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.34,0:40:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Martha feel about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.38,0:40:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now she had to care for everything herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.12,0:40:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we imagine the tension rising
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.46,0:40:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,within Martha’s heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.82,0:40:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The stress level is increased,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.83,0:40:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and her dear sister\Nsits and listens to Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.03,0:40:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So she asked Jesus to correct Mary,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.44,0:40:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to order her back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.24,0:40:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But to her surprise, she, Martha,\Nreceived counsel from Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.08,0:40:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How would we feel in such a situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.98,0:40:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We are doing something well-intentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.42,0:40:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and, yet, instead of commendation,\Nwe receive counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.95,0:40:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe our eyes filled with tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.66,0:40:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel the pain in our chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.06,0:40:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We might think we can’t breathe anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.86,0:40:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Martha think for a moment,\Nreplying to Jesus, saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.73,0:40:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.20,0:40:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am doing everything to support you,\Nand now this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.87,0:41:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“You know, from now on,\NI am listening too,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.67,0:41:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am curious to find out\Nwho prepares the meals for you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.62,0:41:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we don’t know\Nwhat Martha thought and said.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.62,0:41:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we do know,\Nas our printed comment puts it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.42,0:41:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,she took to heart Jesus’ loving correction.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.43,0:41:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What can help us\Nto overcome such a painful moment
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.17,0:41:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and to progress?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.50,0:41:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The term often used in this connection
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.04,0:41:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is “resilience.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.41,0:41:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are resilient\Nare able to recover easily and quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.01,0:41:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from unpleasant and damaging events.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.15,0:41:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It is like the ability of this piece of metal
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.15,0:41:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to tolerate pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.99,0:41:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and go back to its original form.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.22,0:41:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us, therefore,\Nlook at three factors that make us resilient
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.80,0:41:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and different from those\Nwho easily give up and surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.80,0:42:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the first factor is facing reality
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.81,0:42:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—facing reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.17,0:42:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us, please,\Nopen to Proverbs chapter 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.68,0:42:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The question we are asking ourselves\Nin a difficult moment is this:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.48,0:42:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Do I truly understand and accept\Nthe reality of my situation?’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.26,0:42:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, at Proverbs 28:26,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.89,0:42:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it starts by saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.83,0:42:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whoever trusts in his own heart
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.77,0:42:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is stupid.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.13,0:42:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We might tend to put on emotional blinders
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.97,0:42:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and see only what we want to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.98,0:42:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people slip into denial\Nas a coping mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.78,0:42:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Proverb continues\Nin the second part, saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.32,0:42:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the one who walks in wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.32,0:42:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,will escape.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.36,0:43:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This means seeing things the way they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.36,0:43:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Facing reality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.13,0:43:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,—really facing reality is grueling work.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.50,0:43:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, it can be unpleasant
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.10,0:43:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and often emotionally wrenching.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.51,0:43:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Peter had this experience
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.51,0:43:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jesus looked at him\Nafter Peter had denied him three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.02,0:43:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter faced reality, went outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.35,0:43:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,broke down, and wept bitterly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.59,0:43:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,For sure, he was not looking for any excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.16,0:43:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This experience, as well as other situations\Nwhere he received counsel,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.76,0:43:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,helped him to make progress\Nand to fulfill his assignments even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.64,0:43:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what is the second factor?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.04,0:43:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We call it “meaning-making.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.41,0:43:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We might know people who\Nunder pressure threw up their hands
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.81,0:43:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and cried and said,\N“Why is this happening to me?”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.35,0:44:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Such people see themselves as victims,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.35,0:44:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and living through hardship\Ndoes not teach them any lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.63,0:44:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We, however,\Nbased on our Bible knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.03,0:44:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,understand why difficulties\Nand challenging situations
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.33,0:44:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are sometimes unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.63,0:44:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing the bigger picture adds meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.81,0:44:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This helps us, as a resilient person,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.11,0:44:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,not only to endure\Nan unpleasant situation or a new circumstance
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.45,0:44:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but also to look at seeming obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.02,0:44:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and see an opportunity in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.19,0:44:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We all know that no one is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.29,0:44:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone fails at something sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.53,0:44:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So our choice\Nis the manner in which we respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.37,0:44:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We are actively trying\Nto make the best out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.80,0:44:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,looking ahead rather than behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.14,0:44:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,setting goals\N—maybe new goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.78,0:44:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We might remember how Brother Harold King
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.58,0:45:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,showed this resilient disposition
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.62,0:45:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was in solitary confinement.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.69,0:45:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he give meaning\Nto his difficult situation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.42,0:45:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,by making the best out of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.59,0:45:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He said:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.76,0:45:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“I arranged\Nfor a program of ‘preaching’ activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.86,0:45:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“But to whom does one preach\Nwhen in solitary confinement?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.20,0:45:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“I decided that I would build up\Nsome appropriate Bible sermons
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.34,0:45:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the things I could remember
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.54,0:45:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and then preach to imaginary characters.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.05,0:45:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So in our context, we can say
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.52,0:45:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning-making is like building a bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.95,0:45:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,from present day hardships\Nto a better future.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.19,0:45:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of this bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.19,0:45:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we make a difficult situation manageable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.46,0:45:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We remove the sense\Nthat the present is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.97,0:45:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s look at the third factor:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.80,0:46:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a balanced view of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.81,0:46:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said at the beginning\Nthat we have to face reality
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.28,0:46:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which can go along with feelings\Nof sadness and disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.61,0:46:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As resilient people,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.62,0:46:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we don’t take a failure
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.69,0:46:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or a challenging situation personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.56,0:46:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us, please, open to Romans chapter 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.39,0:46:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because we want to demonstrate this point
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.53,0:46:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of the example of the apostle Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.70,0:46:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At times,\Nhe felt discouraged over his weaknesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.44,0:46:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in chapter 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.64,0:46:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,he describes the pain of conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.18,0:46:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that he suffered\Nbecause of feeling captive to sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.18,0:46:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But then in verse 24,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.52,0:46:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,he cries out, saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.85,0:46:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Miserable man that I am!”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.26,0:46:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Evidently, though, Paul realized
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.03,0:46:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that his imperfection did not define him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.03,0:47:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.40,0:47:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in his second letter to his friend Timothy,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.81,0:47:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly before his death,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.81,0:47:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,he stated\Nhis personal conclusion of the matter
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.18,0:47:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,here at 2 Timothy 4:7.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.82,0:47:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He said:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.38,0:47:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have fought the fine fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.99,0:47:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have run the race to the finish,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.96,0:47:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have observed the faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.93,0:47:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul’s problems and inner struggle\Ndid not miraculously disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.87,0:47:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it did not prevent him
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.14,0:47:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,from accomplishing\Nremarkable things in Jehovah’s service.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.74,0:47:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, we do not berate ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.31,0:47:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with self-defeating language,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.32,0:47:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,such as “I’m a failure”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.98,0:47:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or “I’m useless.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.02,0:47:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflecting on positive aspects of our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.32,0:47:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and reflecting on our strengths
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.56,0:48:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to maintain\Na balanced view of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.63,0:48:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So in conclusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.97,0:48:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of Martha reminded us today
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.37,0:48:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the importance of building
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.77,0:48:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and maintaining resilience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.34,0:48:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,by facing reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.91,0:48:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning-making,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.28,0:48:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and maintaining a balanced view of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.85,0:48:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible contains wonderful descriptions
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.86,0:48:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of how life will be in Paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.66,0:48:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As our new music video shows,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.86,0:48:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,visualizing these future blessings
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.97,0:48:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,brings joy to our heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.88,0:49:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I close my eyes, and I can see\NA world of peace, love, and harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.06,0:49:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me,\NAnd you’ll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.16,0:49:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.14,0:49:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not a dream, as I’m sure you know.\NThese things God promised so long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.58,0:49:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Are guaranteed,\NSure to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.99,0:49:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.69,0:49:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Look around—\NThere’s joy and laughter in ev’ry sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.67,0:50:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Look and see—\NThis is the way our God meant it to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.82,0:50:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who fell asleep along the way,\NThey live again; we see them ev’ry day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.66,0:50:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me,\NAnd you’ll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.86,0:50:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.16,0:50:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The pain and crying there used to be\NHas gone forever; now it’s history.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.77,0:51:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me,\NAnd you’ll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.84,0:51:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.48,0:51:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Look around—\NThere’s joy and laughter in ev’ry sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.76,0:51:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Look and see—\NThis is the way our God meant it to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.84,0:51:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s word is enough for me.\NWith eyes of faith, it’s reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.02,0:51:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As we see\NWhat’s in store,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.36,0:51:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be sure\NUntil the moon is no more,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.86,0:52:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When you—
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.77,0:52:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Close your eyes and come with me\NTo God’s world of peace and harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.78,0:52:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me,\NAnd you’ll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.02,0:52:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.29,0:52:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful song and video!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.20,0:52:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In our program,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.20,0:52:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we looked back at theocratic history,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.14,0:52:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,not to be nostalgic, but to remind us
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.04,0:52:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah\Ncontinually improves his organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.05,0:52:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,just as he promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.31,0:52:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We debuted an exciting new series,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.65,0:52:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Our History in Motion,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.39,0:52:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and saw the essential role\Nthat singing plays in our worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.36,0:53:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.86,0:53:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jehovah blesses those
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.50,0:53:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who serve him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.03,0:53:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth gave up
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.57,0:53:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,a glamorous career
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.40,0:53:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but gained spiritual treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.07,0:53:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And we saw that although John
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.44,0:53:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has experienced many difficulties,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.14,0:53:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has helped him
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.01,0:53:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,maintain his joy by helping others.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.98,0:53:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we conclude,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.12,0:53:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s enjoy our video postcard.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.79,0:53:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This month,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.79,0:53:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we visit our brothers in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.30,0:53:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As its name suggests,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.63,0:53:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecuador is situated on earth’s equator.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.54,0:53:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It stretches from the Galapagos Islands
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.14,0:53:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Andes Mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.84,0:53:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Amazon River basin.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.81,0:53:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Mount Chimborazo.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.01,0:53:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Measured from the center of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.05,0:53:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s the highest point on our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.49,0:54:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the bulging\Nof the earth at its equator.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.62,0:54:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This train line was carved\Ninto the Andes more than a century ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.53,0:54:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was used by the first missionaries
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.70,0:54:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,who arrived in 1946.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.10,0:54:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, more than 100,000
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.10,0:54:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nproclaim the good news in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.54,0:54:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly 300,000 people\Nattended the Memorial in 2020.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.31,0:54:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chontapunta Quichua Congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.51,0:54:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,began as an isolated group.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.22,0:54:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To support themselves,\Nour brothers raise flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.15,0:54:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and even pan for gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.76,0:54:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But their zeal is for the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.36,0:54:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They go to great lengths\Nto bear thorough witness in their territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.80,0:54:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where bridges aren’t available,\Nthey find a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.40,0:54:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They use two boats, named Enoc
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.27,0:54:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and Enoc 2, to reach remote\NQuichua-speaking communities.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.31,0:54:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Remote communities\Nhave poor cellular service.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.64,0:55:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn’t stop this Bible student.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.11,0:55:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what he does to get a good signal
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.68,0:55:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can join meetings and have his study.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.22,0:55:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To reach those without cellular service,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.42,0:55:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers use a high-frequency radio
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.09,0:55:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to conduct return visits and Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.06,0:55:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers have arranged for talks\Nand the Memorial to be given in Waorani,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.13,0:55:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,an indigenous language\Nthat’s not yet translated.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.87,0:55:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This little girl, whose family\Nis part of the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.54,0:55:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,shares videos with Waorani-speaking children.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.98,0:55:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She is four years old!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.81,0:55:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Our dear brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.08,0:55:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Chontapunta Quichua Congregation\Nin Ecuador
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.42,0:55:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,send their love and greetings
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.82,0:55:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to the worldwide brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.16,0:55:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Leon, my friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.16,0:55:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to thank you so very much\Nfor helping out with this program.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.43,0:55:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciated the help.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.60,0:55:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And together, we send all of you\Nour warm Christian love.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.61,0:56:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.78,0:56:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.09,0:00:07.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ようこそ 今月のプログラムを視聴\Nしてくださって ありがとうございます
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.32,0:00:10.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日は 親友の\Nレオン･ウィーバー兄弟と一緒です
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.76,0:00:12.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィーバー兄弟 ようこそ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.96,0:00:15.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,お招き ありがとうございます
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.10,0:00:19.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィーバー兄弟について\N少しお話ししたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.37,0:00:22.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は1990年にベテルに来た時
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.74,0:00:24.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕部門に割り当てられました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.01,0:00:28.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこの監督の1人が\Nウィーバー兄弟だったんです
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.14,0:00:32.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕部門ではとても難しい\N問題を扱うことがあるので
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.42,0:00:35.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,アドバイスが欲しいことがありました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.59,0:00:39.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなときはよく\Nウィーバー兄弟に相談しました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.62,0:00:43.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟の事務所に行くと\Nどんなに忙しい時でも手を止めて
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.89,0:00:47.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の話をじっくり聞き\Nアドバイスをくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.93,0:00:51.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕部門でいろいろ\N学べたことに感謝しています
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.47,0:00:54.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィーバー兄弟からも\Nたくさん学ぶことができました
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.94,0:01:00.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう訳で 兄弟のことが\N大好きですし 尊敬しています
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.04,0:01:05.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィーバー兄弟 今月は\Nどんなプログラムでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.28,0:01:07.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,何十年も前 バルネーブ姉妹は
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.78,0:01:11.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにもっと仕えるために\N華やかな仕事を辞めました
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:15.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,その結果 姉妹の人生は\Nどう変わりましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.93,0:01:18.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しいシリーズも始まります
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.50,0:01:23.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の歴史のさまざまな面に\Nスポットが当てられます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.13,0:01:26.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと新たな発見があるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.34,0:01:30.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは楽しみですね\Nお見逃しなく
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.74,0:01:36.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,2021年11月の\NJW Broadcasting®です
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.63,0:01:57.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言者イザヤを通して
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.70,0:02:00.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは素晴らしい約束をしました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.30,0:02:02.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは今実現しています
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.41,0:02:07.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでみましょう\Nイザヤ 60:17です
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.24,0:02:12.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は銅を金に替え
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.52,0:02:17.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄を銀に 木を銅に
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.12,0:02:19.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,石を鉄に替える
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:22.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和をあなたの監督とし
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.66,0:02:26.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,正義をあなたの管理者とする」
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:29.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここにある「監督」とか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:31.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,「管理者」という言葉は
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.70,0:02:33.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,組織をイメージさせます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.77,0:02:36.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはどんなことを言っていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.21,0:02:38.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは組織の取り決めが
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.64,0:02:43.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,徐々に良くなっていくのを\N見ることができる ということです
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.08,0:02:46.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年エホバに仕えてきた方なら
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.32,0:02:51.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤのこの預言が実現してきたことに\N同意なさると思います
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.55,0:02:58.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,この話では 第2次世界大戦後の\N進展について振り返りたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.86,0:03:01.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人が過ごしてきた時代です
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.56,0:03:05.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,これから取り上げることを\N初めて聞く方もいるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.64,0:03:08.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際に経験してきた方もいると思います
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.67,0:03:12.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう方にとっては\N懐かしい思い出でしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.08,0:03:14.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,では タイムスリップを楽しみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.54,0:03:19.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,話の主題は \N「あの頃を覚えていますか」です
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:24.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,第2次世界大戦前\Nまたその後何年もの間
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:27.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの会衆は王国会館を\N持っていませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.82,0:03:30.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際その頃は 個人の家や
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.59,0:03:34.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,借りた施設で集まるよう\N勧められていました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.16,0:03:37.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,借りた施設や個人の家を使う方が
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:40.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,融通が利く という理由でした
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:45.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要に応じて 集会を開く場所を\N簡単に変えることができました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:47.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも不便な点もありました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:50.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の団体が同じ場所を\N使うこともあったので
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.71,0:03:52.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会が終わった後
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.75,0:03:58.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,文書 雑誌 演台 音響装置を\N置いたままにすることはできません
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.99,0:04:04.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう物を全部まとめて\N持って帰らなければなりませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:06.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.03,0:04:09.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,会場にかなり早く着いて
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.17,0:04:11.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,掃除しなければならない\Nこともありました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.73,0:04:15.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,マナーが悪い人たちが\N使った後は特にそうです
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.31,0:04:18.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,その中にたばこを吸う人たちが\Nいたら 大変でした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.91,0:04:21.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会前に空気を入れ換えようとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.88,0:04:24.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう簡単にはいきません
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.18,0:04:29.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時は 民間の会場でたばこを\N吸うことが許されていました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.19,0:04:32.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,飛行機でも\Nほとんどどこでもそうでした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.26,0:04:35.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 私たちは大変でした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:37.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかにも問題がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:41.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの生まれ故郷で\N王国会館ができる前のことです
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.93,0:04:43.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆が借りていた会場は
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.97,0:04:46.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,10月にはハロウィーンの\N飾り付けが行われ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.00,0:04:51.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,12月にはステージに大きな\Nクリスマスツリーが置かれました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.31,0:04:53.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,撤去できませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.38,0:04:56.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時カナダでは そうした会場に
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.25,0:04:58.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,英国の王と女王の絵が飾られ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.98,0:05:01.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,国旗が掲げられていました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれも撤去できませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.02,0:05:10.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも 聖書に関心を持つ\N多くの人たちが集会に出席しました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.39,0:05:12.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席者は会場の様子よりも
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.96,0:05:17.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこで話される事柄に\N注意を向けていたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.43,0:05:19.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,当初会衆は
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.47,0:05:24.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分たちだけで王国会館を\N建てなければなりませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.41,0:05:29.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,中には 土地を買うだけの\Nお金しかない会衆もありました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:32.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 建物を建てる\Nお金を集めるために
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:36.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,何年もかかる場合もありました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.79,0:05:39.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえお金が集まったとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.16,0:05:43.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,建設のための技術を持つ兄弟たちの\N数は限られていました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.86,0:05:45.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,1人か2人の兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.93,0:05:50.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,時々週末を使って 一生懸命働きました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.23,0:05:54.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちの頑張りには\N頭が下がる思いです
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:58.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は 支部設計建設部門の監督の下
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.17,0:06:01.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,大勢のボランティアが短期間で
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.28,0:06:05.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,使いやすい王国会館を建設しています
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:07.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会はどうでしたか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.65,0:06:10.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年 神権宣教学校も奉仕会も
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.65,0:06:15.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の書籍研究も\N「ものみの塔」研究も約1時間でした
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.93,0:06:20.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,時々行われていた公開講演もです
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.16,0:06:23.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,公開講演は毎週あった\Nわけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.70,0:06:28.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし講演者がいれば 4つとか8つの\N一連の話が行われました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.81,0:06:33.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後しばらく 公開講演は\N行われなくなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:35.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.38,0:06:40.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,神権宣教学校が始まったのは\N1943年です
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.32,0:06:44.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちが1時間の話を\N行えるようになるまでには
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.35,0:06:46.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間がかかりました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:50.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもやがて 素晴らしい公開講演を\N行えるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:53.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,公開講演のたびに ビラが準備され
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,講演者の名前も印刷されて\Nいたことを覚えていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.34,0:07:02.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,1959年まで
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.54,0:07:05.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,入校できるのは兄弟だけでした
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.81,0:07:10.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時はまず 生徒の\N出席確認が行われていました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.35,0:07:14.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,入校している兄弟全員の\N名前が読み上げられました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:18.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,名前が呼ばれたら 「はい」と\N言うことになっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.12,0:07:20.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,「来てまーす」なんて\N言う人もいましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.36,0:07:22.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,「はい」と答えるべきでした
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:25.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,その頃の指示によると
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.06,0:07:28.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,しばらくの期間\Nきちんとした理由もなく
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.20,0:07:33.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,習慣的に休むなら 退学させられる\Nことになっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.44,0:07:37.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 この指示は変更されました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:41.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席確認というと ちょっとした\N事件を思い出します
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.21,0:07:45.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの会衆で毎週\N生徒たちの名前が呼ばれる時
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.92,0:07:51.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,私より少しだけ年上の兄弟たちが\N「はい」と答えていました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.25,0:07:53.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,それである日 学校の僕に
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.86,0:07:57.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,「次回から私の名前も\N呼んでください」とお願いしました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.86,0:08:00.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は私を心から褒めてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.90,0:08:03.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,翌週 私の名前が呼ばれると
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.67,0:08:07.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会後 みんなが褒めてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:10.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,「なんでだろう\N『はい』って言っただけなのに」
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.71,0:08:12.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は知らなかったんですが
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.74,0:08:17.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,名前が呼ばれるということは\N話もする ということでした
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:20.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はただ 名前を呼んで\Nほしかっただけなんです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.65,0:08:25.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,2カ月後 1953年4月8日に
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.29,0:08:27.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めての8分の話をしました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.99,0:08:31.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は 「世の終わりを\Nふれ告げる」です
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.03,0:08:35.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時は聖書朗読が\Nなかったので 話をしました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.63,0:08:40.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校に入ると 8分の話を\Nすることになっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.77,0:08:45.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん今は 週日の集会の\N生徒になるというのがどういうことか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:48.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな分かっているはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.31,0:08:50.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,1950年には
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.35,0:08:54.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,英語の「クリスチャン･ギリシャ語聖書\N新世界訳」が発表され
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.28,0:08:57.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会に持ってくるよう勧められました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:09:00.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ語聖書の方は\N「アメリカ標準訳」か 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.52,0:09:02.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ジェームズ王欽定訳」を使いました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.89,0:09:07.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの名が出てくる「アメリカ\N標準訳」を使う人が多かったです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.56,0:09:10.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 集会には ヘブライ語聖書と
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.47,0:09:13.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,「クリスチャン･ギリシャ語聖書\N新世界訳」を持っていきました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.97,0:09:16.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,2冊だけです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.57,0:09:20.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 「ヘブライ語聖書\N新世界訳」が
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:22.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,1巻ずつ発表されました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.88,0:09:25.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,1, 2年に1巻受け取りました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.31,0:09:27.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しいものを受け取るたびに
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.38,0:09:30.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会に持ってくるよう勧められました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:33.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,その数はだんだん増えていき
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.39,0:09:35.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,1960年には
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.73,0:09:39.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ語聖書が全部で\N5巻になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.40,0:09:42.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに加えて ギリシャ語聖書と
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:44.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の出版物を持っていきました
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.33,0:09:46.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかも分厚い本です
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.47,0:09:50.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 大きくて丈夫な\Nかばんが必要でした
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.67,0:09:53.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,「新世界訳聖書」が1冊になった時には
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.51,0:09:55.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当にうれしかったです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.54,0:09:58.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,1961年のことです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.68,0:10:02.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,音楽についてはどうでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.15,0:10:05.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は音楽が大好きです
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.42,0:10:09.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年 会衆の集会でどの歌を歌うかは
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.63,0:10:11.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆に任されていました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:15.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会の司会者が歌を選びました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.20,0:10:18.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもその歌を歌えないこともありました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.87,0:10:23.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの王国会館には 伴奏用に\Nピアノなどの楽器がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.61,0:10:27.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,伴奏者は全ての曲を\N演奏できたわけではないので
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.44,0:10:30.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人が演奏できる曲しか\N歌えませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.61,0:10:34.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ曲を何度も歌ったので\N覚えてしまうほどでした
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.95,0:10:39.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,伴奏者は私たちのために\N頑張って演奏してくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.49,0:10:43.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんな感じだったので\N70年近くたった今でも
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:47.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時歌った歌を思い出すことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:50.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは覚えていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.83,0:10:53.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,筆記の復習です
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.27,0:10:56.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,筆記の復習では 過去数週間に
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.14,0:11:00.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,神権宣教学校で学んだ\N事柄を振り返りました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.88,0:11:05.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,30分で 25ぐらいの質問に答えます
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.38,0:11:07.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,30分たつと
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.48,0:11:10.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれ自分の名前を書いて
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.15,0:11:12.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校の僕に提出します
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.89,0:11:16.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校の僕はそれを家で採点しました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.43,0:11:18.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,質問が25あれば
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.56,0:11:20.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,1問につき4点で
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.76,0:11:23.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,合計100点になります
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.70,0:11:28.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,翌週 学校の僕から答案が返されます
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.34,0:11:31.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はよく覚えていますが 昔は
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:36.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の最高点と最低点が\N発表されました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.48,0:11:41.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,幸い その人たちの名前は\N発表されませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.42,0:11:46.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて 点数を発表する\N取り決めはなくなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.69,0:11:49.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,巡回大会が金曜日の夕方から
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.46,0:11:53.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,日曜日の午後まで行われて\Nいたことを覚えていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.83,0:11:58.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,土曜日は午後から夜まで\Nプログラムが続きました
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.37,0:12:01.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,土曜日の夜は特に面白かったです
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.54,0:12:03.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,生き生きとした実演があったので
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:07.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後まで目が離せませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:11.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,かなり凝ったステージのセットが\N造られることもありました
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.78,0:12:16.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 伝道者が家から家の\N伝道をする実演がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.89,0:12:20.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,今なら ドアを実際に\N準備することはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.56,0:12:23.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも当時の巡回大会では
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.29,0:12:26.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ステージ上にドアのセットが\N造られることもありました
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.96,0:12:30.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご丁寧に呼び鈴まで\N付けられることもありました
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.97,0:12:35.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,家の人が関心を示すだろうということは\Nすぐに分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.04,0:12:38.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,家の番号が777だったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.74,0:12:41.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,家の人が敵対的な場合も分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.54,0:12:45.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,家の番号が666だったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:47.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある実演を思い出します
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.48,0:12:51.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道者がドアをノックすると\N司祭の格好をした兄弟が出てきます
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:55.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,三位一体について議論を吹っ掛けます
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.89,0:12:57.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,大胆な演出ですね
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.93,0:13:02.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも1度見たら忘れられない\N視覚教材です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.77,0:13:09.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは覚えていますか 昔は会衆に\N会衆の僕と ほかに7人の僕がいました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.87,0:13:13.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の僕の補佐 聖書研究の僕
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.18,0:13:16.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,会計の僕 「ものみの塔」研究の僕
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.41,0:13:19.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,雑誌と区域の僕 文書の僕
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.38,0:13:21.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,神権宣教学校の僕です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.68,0:13:24.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 書籍研究の司会者を除くと
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.02,0:13:29.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆で奉仕する僕は最高8人でした
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.63,0:13:32.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かが引っ越して空きができない限り
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.80,0:13:36.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い兄弟は僕になれませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.53,0:13:40.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 若い兄弟には責任を\N担う道がないのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:44.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに ミカ 5:5に\N記されている預言は
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.87,0:13:47.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように実現するのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:49.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこう約束していました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.41,0:13:51.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私たちはアッシリア人に対して
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.71,0:13:55.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,7人の牧者 いや \N8人の高官を立てる」
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:13:58.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,7は完全にそろっているという意味です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.99,0:14:01.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから8人の高官とは
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.06,0:14:03.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆を教え導く兄弟たちが
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.79,0:14:06.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,十分過ぎるほどいるということです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.46,0:14:10.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 会衆で8人の僕しか\N奉仕できないのであれば
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.87,0:14:12.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたらいいのでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.97,0:14:16.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,答えは1971年に与えられました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.74,0:14:19.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆で長老団が奉仕するようになること
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.98,0:14:24.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,また長老や奉仕の僕の数に\N上限がないことを知って
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.28,0:14:29.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,うれしく思いました 資格があれば\N誰でも任命されるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.39,0:14:34.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が66年前にバプテスマを受けた時
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.92,0:14:38.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の僕たちの承認を得る\N必要はありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.83,0:14:41.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマ希望者が答えるのは
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.06,0:14:46.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマの話の最後に\N行われる2つの質問だけでした
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:51.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 時には兄弟たちが\Nびっくりするようなことも起きました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.14,0:14:53.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマの話が終わる頃
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.34,0:14:57.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かが会場の前の方に急いでやって来て
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.05,0:14:59.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つの質問に答え
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.35,0:15:02.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを受けたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.38,0:15:05.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしバプテスマを受けるには
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.15,0:15:07.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマの意味をよく理解し
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.99,0:15:12.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の原則に沿って\N生活していることが求められます
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.46,0:15:17.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 1967年に\Nバプテスマ希望者が
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.20,0:15:22.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当にバプテスマを受ける資格が\Nあるかどうかを確認するための質問が
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.14,0:15:24.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,準備されました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.34,0:15:27.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 それらの質問は何度か調整され
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:33.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,今はバプテスマ希望者と60ほどの\N質問を討議することになっています
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.58,0:15:36.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,銅が金に替わったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.29,0:15:41.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,出版物にあまり挿絵が\Nなかったことを覚えていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.42,0:15:46.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,挿絵があっても たいていは\N白黒か 2色の絵でした
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.63,0:15:52.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,今ではフルカラーの魅力的な\N出版物が作られています
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.64,0:15:57.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,外国語会衆で奉仕してきた兄弟姉妹は
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.94,0:16:00.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい出版物が英語で出ても
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.58,0:16:02.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分が学んでいる言語のものは
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.61,0:16:05.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,何年も待つ必要があったことを\N覚えているでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.81,0:16:09.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,研究記事も何カ月か待ちました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.49,0:16:14.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,各地の支部では 同時出版が\Nまだ行われていませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.22,0:16:16.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時はこんな感じでした
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.26,0:16:19.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,英語の原稿が翻訳のために
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.23,0:16:22.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,各地の支部に郵送されます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.06,0:16:26.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,翻訳者たちが英語の文章の\N意味について尋ねたい場合
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.87,0:16:30.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,質問の手紙を本部に郵送します
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.94,0:16:34.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後本部は回答を支部に送ります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.74,0:16:38.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,こういうやり取りには\Nかなりの時間がかかりました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.05,0:16:41.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,郵便事情が悪い国もありました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.62,0:16:46.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では 兄弟姉妹が開発した\N特別なプログラムのおかげで
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:49.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,電子的にやり取りが\Nできるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.66,0:16:52.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかにもさまざまな点が改善され
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.29,0:16:56.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほとんどの言語が英語と同時出版\Nできるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.67,0:16:59.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,何という進歩でしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:02.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のことはご存じでしたか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.14,0:17:04.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆内外を問わず
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.17,0:17:07.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,出版物のための寄付を\N求めないという決定が
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.84,0:17:12.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,米国で下されてから\Nかれこれ31年ほどになります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.98,0:17:16.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて全世界でそのように\Nすることになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.55,0:17:20.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹はこのことを本当に喜びました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.62,0:17:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 出版物のための\N寄付が求められていた頃
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:28.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,アフリカなどの兄弟たちの中には
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.13,0:17:32.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族全員分の「ものみの塔」を\N入手できない人たちがいました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:35.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても貧しかったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.74,0:17:38.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,製本など手に入りません
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんなことがありました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.14,0:17:43.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,アフリカのある宣教者は\N1人の若い兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.68,0:17:47.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,コメントでいろいろな聖句を\N使っていることに気付きました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.68,0:17:50.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,感心した宣教者はこう尋ねました
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.32,0:17:53.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「どうしてそんなにたくさんの\N聖句を知っているの？」
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.02,0:18:00.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い兄弟は 「『論じる』の本があるときに\Nいつも読んでいるんです」と答えました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.36,0:18:05.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者は 「本があるときに読むって\Nどういう意味？」と尋ねました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.67,0:18:07.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い兄弟は言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.70,0:18:11.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,「僕は『論じる』の本を持ってないんです\Nお金がないので
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.51,0:18:16.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 『論じる』の本を持っている\N姉妹がいるので 時々借りています
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.85,0:18:21.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,借りている間はいつも\N読むようにしているんです」
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.25,0:18:23.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者はどうしたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:25.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに「論じる」の本と
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.62,0:18:29.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,「新世界訳聖書」を\N若い兄弟にプレゼントしました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.76,0:18:31.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするだけの価値がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.93,0:18:34.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 若い兄弟は\Nどうなったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.63,0:18:36.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルに招待され
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.70,0:18:39.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,文書部門に割り当てられました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.40,0:18:43.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は文書の大切さが\Nよく分かっていたので
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.07,0:18:48.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆に必要な文書が届くように\N一生懸命に奉仕しました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.34,0:18:52.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,振り返ってみると どの取り決めも
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.45,0:18:55.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時のニーズにかなったものでした
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:57.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,良質の銅のようなものです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.82,0:19:00.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは劣ったものとは見ていません
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.42,0:19:05.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろ ゼカリヤ 4:10に\Nあるような見方をしています
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.96,0:19:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「小さな始まりの日を\N軽く見たのは誰か」
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.33,0:19:13.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 責任を持つ兄弟たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.80,0:19:17.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,より良い方法を見つけると\Nためらわずに調整しました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.57,0:19:19.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に信仰が強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.91,0:19:24.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,これからも より良いものに\Nなっていくことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:30.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初に述べた通り 皆さんにとって\N初めて聞く話もあったかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.19,0:19:32.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年奉仕している人に
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.22,0:19:35.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理を学んだ頃のことを\N尋ねてみるのはどうですか
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.86,0:19:41.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと 楽しくて励みになる\Nエピソードをたくさん聞けるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.26,0:19:45.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深い歴史を話してくださり\Nありがとうございました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.93,0:19:48.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで 本当に大きな\N変化がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.84,0:19:51.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここ数十年の間にです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.07,0:19:54.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは確かに ご自分の組織を
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.18,0:19:57.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,絶えずより良いものにしています
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.68,0:20:02.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ある兄弟の手本に注目しましょう\Nジョン･ミルズ兄弟です
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.35,0:20:06.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は これまで取り上げた\Nさまざまな変化を見てきました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:09.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,個人的にも大きな変化がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.83,0:20:14.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は長年 さまざまな割り当てを\N忠実に果たしてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.66,0:20:17.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 難しい問題もありました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:23.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,私には3人の姉がいます
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:26.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,母が真理を教えてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.01,0:20:29.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,よくソファーに座って
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.14,0:20:33.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,母と聖書のことを話したのを\N思い出します
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.05,0:20:41.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,母は「どんな割り当ても 感謝して\N大切にするんだよ」と教えてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:46.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓奉仕は私の生きがいでした
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.96,0:20:51.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギレアデに行けば他の人にもっと\N与えることができると思いました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.30,0:20:54.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕に打ち込めます\Nエホバにこう祈りました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.57,0:20:56.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ギレアデに行きたいです
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.91,0:21:01.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして もしできれば\N妻も与えてください」
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:07.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそうお願いしてから ちょっと\N厚かましいかなと思いました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.12,0:21:11.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバは願いを\Nかなえてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:14.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてギレアデに行きました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.09,0:21:16.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,驚いたことに
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.39,0:21:23.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,すごくきれいで信仰の強い姉妹が
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:25.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じクラスにいたんです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.57,0:21:27.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイスです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.17,0:21:34.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは ギレアデを卒業して\N1週間後に結婚しました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.28,0:21:39.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者ホームでほかの7人と一緒に
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.25,0:21:44.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,新婚生活をスタートさせるのはちょっと\Nと思うかもしれませんが
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.75,0:21:49.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは平気でした\Nハネムーン気分でした
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.26,0:21:52.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロンビアでの伝道は最高です
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.33,0:21:54.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,満喫しました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.20,0:21:58.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,願っていた生き方です
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.43,0:22:03.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイスは人々を教えるのが\Nとても上手でした
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.97,0:22:06.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,私をよく支えてくれて
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.17,0:22:10.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に奉仕をするのが楽しかったです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.68,0:22:14.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロンビアは治安がとても悪いです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.72,0:22:18.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,時には 状況が非常に悪化しました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.45,0:22:21.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,朝 出掛ける時にお互いの顔を見て
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.82,0:22:26.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,「もし何かあったら楽園で会おうね」\Nと言うこともありました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.13,0:22:31.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロンビアは第二の\Nふるさとになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.73,0:22:36.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろいろな割り当てで\N国中を旅行しました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:41.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロンビアでの奉仕を始めて\N20年余りたった頃
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.51,0:22:45.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイスの母親を世話する\N必要が生じました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.88,0:22:50.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのためにはコロンビアを\N離れなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.15,0:22:56.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロンビアを去るのは胸が\N張り裂けるような思いでした
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.03,0:23:01.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさんの奉仕の割り当てを\N手放すのは寂しいことでした
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.70,0:23:04.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれも愛着のある奉仕だったので
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.90,0:23:09.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,米国に行ってからも
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.67,0:23:12.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人で協力しました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.74,0:23:15.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイスは置かれた状況でベストを尽くし
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.74,0:23:19.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,何でも計画的に行いました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.55,0:23:22.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,母親を本当によく世話していました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.02,0:23:27.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすることに深い喜びを\N感じていました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.52,0:23:32.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人を助けるのが\Nロイスの生き方でした
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.63,0:23:37.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな立場や責任を与えられているかは
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.10,0:23:39.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,重要ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.57,0:23:43.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の幸せというものは
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.77,0:23:47.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,与えることから得られます
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.64,0:23:51.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 ロイスは重い病気になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.28,0:23:56.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 病気のことで泣いたり\N自分を哀れんだりしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.42,0:23:58.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもほかの人のことを考え
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.05,0:24:01.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けになろうとしていました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.62,0:24:06.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,痛みを感じる時も そうしていたんです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.10,0:24:10.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロイスは亡くなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.30,0:24:15.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,今でも ロイスの立派な\N生き方のことをよく考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.94,0:24:20.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすると 自分も\N頑張ろうという気持ちになります
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.34,0:24:23.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,この中央アメリカ支部では
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.68,0:24:26.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい兄弟姉妹と\N一緒に奉仕しています
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.98,0:24:29.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の家族です
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.12,0:24:32.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻を亡くすという経験をした時
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.09,0:24:34.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に決めたことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.62,0:24:38.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,つらい経験をしている\N兄弟姉妹に気付いたなら
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.93,0:24:42.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に時間を過ごすことです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.66,0:24:47.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,座ってコーヒーでも\N飲みながら話をします
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.70,0:24:51.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間の兄弟姉妹を気遣い
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.47,0:24:55.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,思いやり 励ますことは
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.18,0:24:58.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,私にとって大きな喜びです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.71,0:25:03.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 私自身が難しい状況を\N耐え忍ぶ上で
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.82,0:25:07.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても助けになっています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.46,0:25:14.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年エホバに忠実に仕えてきた\Nミルズ兄弟の姿を見て 
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.46,0:25:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリント第二 1:3, 4の言葉の\N通りだと思いました こうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.04,0:25:26.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,「［エホバは］私たちがどんな試練に\N遭うとしても慰めてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.78,0:25:30.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで私たちは 神からの慰めにより
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.01,0:25:35.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな試練に遭う人をも\N慰めることができます」
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.52,0:25:39.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて こう思ったことはありますか
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.49,0:25:42.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,「集会で歌を歌うのはなぜだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.69,0:25:48.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,地区大会はどうしていつも\N夏に開かれるのだろう」
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.03,0:25:52.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い皆さんやバプテスマを\N受けて間もない方は
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.63,0:25:57.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の歴史について\N詳しく知らないかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.31,0:26:01.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の歴史は貴重な財産です
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.18,0:26:03.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんの相続財産です
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.78,0:26:07.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜひ受け取ってほしいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.12,0:26:10.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 統治体の承認の下
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.09,0:26:14.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しいシリーズが\N始まることになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.19,0:26:19.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,「JWヒストリー」です
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.33,0:26:24.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎回 私たちの崇拝の\N1つの面が取り上げられます
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.97,0:26:28.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,スプレーン兄弟の話も\N興味深かったですね
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.80,0:26:30.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,このシリーズを通して
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.84,0:26:33.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの崇拝の基盤が
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.58,0:26:36.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝統や習慣ではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.41,0:26:41.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉の真理であることが\N分かるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.12,0:26:45.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,これから見る第1回では
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.35,0:26:51.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを賛美する歌の歴史を\N取り上げたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.26,0:26:56.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは極秘に作られ
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.83,0:26:59.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジャケットの裏地に隠され
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.97,0:27:03.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひそかに国外に運ばれました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.17,0:27:05.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,何がですか
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.24,0:27:11.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,シベリアの兄弟姉妹が歌った\N王国の歌の録音テープです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.45,0:27:15.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,このテープは地球の反対側に運ばれ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.02,0:27:21.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,1958年にニューヨークで開かれた\N国際大会で流されました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.69,0:27:26.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,25万人以上の聴衆が\Nそれを聞いたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.46,0:27:31.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌うことがエホバの証人にとって\Nそれほど大切なのはなぜですか
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.63,0:27:36.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,「JWヒストリー」の第1回を\Nご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.51,0:27:49.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを崇拝する人たちは何千年もの間
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.32,0:27:52.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌でエホバを賛美してきました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.19,0:27:54.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,では現代 どんないきさつで
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.59,0:27:57.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,崇拝のために歌うように\Nなったのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.76,0:28:01.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,話は150年以上前にさかのぼります
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.26,0:28:03.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,1869年
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.53,0:28:06.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,米国ペンシルバニア州アレゲーニーで
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.60,0:28:08.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,若いチャールズ･テイズ･ラッセルは
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.00,0:28:12.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の真理を探し求めていました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.41,0:28:15.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある晩 道を歩いていると
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.18,0:28:19.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,地下の部屋から賛美歌が\N聞こえてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.62,0:28:23.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,中に入って話を聞くと
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.18,0:28:28.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,それまでにないほど聖書を学びたい\Nという気持ちが強まりました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.12,0:28:31.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 ラッセルと仲間たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.06,0:28:33.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の真理をいっそう理解し
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.90,0:28:37.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,清い崇拝で音楽を使うようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.73,0:28:42.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラッセルの父親は一時期\N音楽に関係した仕事をしていました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.74,0:28:45.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういうこともあってラッセルは
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.07,0:28:48.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,音楽には感情を動かす\N大きな力があることを
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.58,0:28:50.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく知っていたのかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.81,0:28:53.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,「真理を述べた歌を歌うのは
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.15,0:29:00.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の民にとって真理を心と頭の中に\N収める良い方法」だと思っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.46,0:29:04.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,1879年7月に出版された
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.13,0:29:06.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,「シオンのものみの塔」の創刊号で
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.96,0:29:10.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の歌の本が発表されました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.43,0:29:13.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,「花嫁の歌」という本です
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.64,0:29:17.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,144曲の賛美歌が収められていました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.74,0:29:20.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書研究者たちはその本を使って
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.98,0:29:23.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会や大会で歌いました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.75,0:29:25.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,1900年代初め
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.85,0:29:29.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした歌はどんな感じで\N歌われていたのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.48,0:29:34.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,チャールズ･テイズ･ラッセルの講演会に\N来たところを想像してみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.32,0:29:38.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,中に入ると 小さな紙を渡されます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.29,0:29:41.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,席を探しますが 満席です
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.33,0:29:43.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,聴衆が静かになると
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.63,0:29:48.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,講演会は歌と祈りで\N始まることが知らされます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.27,0:29:52.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般の教会の座席には\N賛美歌の本がありますが
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.31,0:29:54.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここは借りた会場です
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.64,0:29:56.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,先ほど受け取った紙を見ると
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.95,0:29:59.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌の歌詞が書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.81,0:30:05.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を学びたい人が自分の名前と\N住所を書く欄もあります
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.79,0:30:10.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,聴衆が歌い始めると\Nあなたもそれに加わります
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.73,0:30:14.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時の歌はどんな\N感じだったのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.13,0:30:18.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,80年以上歌われた\Nある歌を聞いてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.73,0:30:24.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,1916年に録音された\N「たたえよ」という歌です
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.24,0:30:33.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,今の歌とはちょっと雰囲気が違いますね
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.35,0:30:35.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,この歌は 長年の間に
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.92,0:30:39.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌詞やタイトルが何度か変わりました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.72,0:30:43.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは1935年のものです
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.93,0:30:48.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ものみの塔男性四重唱団が歌っています
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.21,0:31:01.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の歌の本では この歌は
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.78,0:31:05.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,「イエスの御名の力をたたえよ」\Nという題でした
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.85,0:31:08.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの名の力について歌ったもので
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.85,0:31:11.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは全く出てきません
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.72,0:31:17.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時の歌の多くは 一般の教会の\N賛美歌がベースになっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.96,0:31:21.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ歌の1950年版です
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.03,0:31:25.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの名を過度に強調するのではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.10,0:31:29.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の望むことを知らせるよう\N勧める歌詞になっていて
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.30,0:31:32.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの名が出てきます
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.88,0:31:40.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ変わったのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.45,0:31:44.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の真理の最新の理解に\N合わせるためです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.82,0:31:48.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,光が明るさを増すにつれ
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.32,0:31:53.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理をいっそう理解できるようになり\N歌も変わりました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.26,0:31:55.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の歌の本には
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.30,0:31:58.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,「間違った教えの影響を受けていない歌」\Nを出版することを
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.00,0:32:01.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,目指している と述べられています
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.77,0:32:04.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も同じことを目指しています
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.07,0:32:10.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは 伝統や愛着に\N縛られることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.65,0:32:14.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが歌うのは真理の歌です
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.15,0:32:17.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,1928年の歌の本は
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.95,0:32:20.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな転換点になりました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.66,0:32:25.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹の作った歌がたくさん\N使われるようになったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.16,0:32:31.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの名 性質 王国にいっそう\N注意が向けられるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.30,0:32:35.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,本のタイトルも\N「エホバに奉る讃歌」となっています
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.97,0:32:41.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,この歌のように 皆さんもご存じの\N歌も含まれていました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.15,0:32:55.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご両親はエホバの証人ですか\Nおじいさん おばあさん
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.96,0:32:59.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひいおじいさん ひいおばあさん\Nの代からですか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.06,0:33:01.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしそうなら 集会や大会で
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.73,0:33:04.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,代々同じ歌を歌ってきたことになります
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.97,0:33:07.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさに相続財産です
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.67,0:33:11.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 1940年代の\N状況を見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.81,0:33:15.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰ゆえに投獄されていた\N兄弟たちもいます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.51,0:33:19.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界大戦が行われており\N良い知らせが必要でした
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.91,0:33:22.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教活動が強化され
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.08,0:33:27.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,ものみの塔ギレアデ聖書学校と\N神権宣教学校が始まりました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.82,0:33:33.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 集会で再び歌が\N歌われるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.40,0:33:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,えっ？歌が再び歌われるようになった？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.03,0:33:42.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,実は 集会で歌が歌われていない\N時期があったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.17,0:33:44.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつのことですか
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.07,0:33:48.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,次回の「JWヒストリー」をお楽しみに
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.29,0:34:01.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,うーん 続きが楽しみです
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.42,0:34:04.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌が歌われていなかった\N時期があるなんて
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.69,0:34:07.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと意外ですね
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.70,0:34:11.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,続きはパート2をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.17,0:34:15.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,近いうちにjw.orgに\Nアップされます
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.34,0:34:17.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,今後「JWヒストリー」では
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.01,0:34:20.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,さまざまな内容が取り上げられます
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.61,0:34:22.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,楽しみですね
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.41,0:34:26.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,40年ほど前の「目ざめよ！」に
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.25,0:34:31.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,エリザベス･バルネーブ姉妹の\Nライフ･ストーリーが載せられています
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.05,0:34:38.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,バルネーブ姉妹は 自分の生き方を\N大きく変えた理由を述べています
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.89,0:34:42.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 姉妹は\Nどうしているのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.76,0:34:46.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,今回の「あの人は今」をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.57,0:34:49.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹のその後が分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.47,0:34:58.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,子供の頃から\Nバレリーナになるのが夢でした
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.88,0:35:03.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 幼いうちから\Nレッスンを始めました
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.89,0:35:06.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ディレクターへの絶対的な服従と
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.72,0:35:10.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,バレエ団への忠誠をたたき込まれました
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.16,0:35:13.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,バレエを何よりも優先することもです
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.00,0:35:21.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,この世界で成功するには 全てのものを\N犠牲にしなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.47,0:35:23.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそんなの無理ですし
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.50,0:35:27.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような生き方はむなしいだけです
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.08,0:35:33.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも そういう世界に足を踏み入れると
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.02,0:35:37.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,きらびやかな生き方に\N魅了されてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.35,0:35:39.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのまま進んでいって
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.42,0:35:42.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分がコントロールされている\Nだけだと気付いても
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.36,0:35:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこから抜け出すのは大変です
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.03,0:35:48.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は若い人たちに\Nよく言っているんですが
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.30,0:35:52.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,この世界での成功がどんなに\N素晴らしいものに見えても 
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.27,0:35:56.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,その釣り糸の先には\N鋭い釣り針が付いています
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.50,0:36:00.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある時 がんじがらめになっている\N自分に気付きます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.61,0:36:03.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこから抜け出すのは大変です
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.68,0:36:08.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンのわなは強力なので\Nそう簡単には出られません
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.55,0:36:11.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,気付かないうちにそうなってしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.52,0:36:14.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,バレエには厳しい練習が必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.52,0:36:16.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも何とかしてスキルを身に付け
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.82,0:36:19.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを実践できるように\Nなる必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.96,0:36:23.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間はかかりましたが\Nできるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.33,0:36:25.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,練習すれば結果は付いてきます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.90,0:36:30.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも並大抵の努力では\Nスキルは身に付きません
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.67,0:36:34.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,1987年までベテルで奉仕しました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.54,0:36:39.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルを出た後 夫はすぐに\N仕事を始めることができました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.25,0:36:43.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも私は健康上の問題があって\N働けませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.68,0:36:46.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,5カ月ぐらいずっと寝込んでいました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.35,0:36:49.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 体調はだんだん良くなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.76,0:36:52.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも治療費が大変なことに\Nなっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.66,0:36:57.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても寝てはいられないと思い\Nパートタイムの仕事を探しました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.60,0:37:00.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫と私はエホバにずっと祈っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.74,0:37:04.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが必ず助けてくれる\Nと信じていました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.57,0:37:07.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,何とか 法律事務所で\N働けることになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.78,0:37:11.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,とてもいい仕事でした\N30年働きました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.71,0:37:16.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私の努力を\N本当に祝福してくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.35,0:37:18.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,仕事を頑張って続けました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.72,0:37:21.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもいつもエホバを第一にしました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.92,0:37:24.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい仕事にもだんだん慣れて
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.23,0:37:27.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,やり方も分かってきたので\Nこう祈りました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.56,0:37:31.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ 私はこの新しい\N仕事を覚えました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.20,0:37:33.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたのために活用したいです」
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.53,0:37:35.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて ベテルの法律部門で
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.77,0:37:38.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,コミューターとして\N働くようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.64,0:37:41.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルを出て 11年後だと思いますが
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.28,0:37:44.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,仕事中に突然具合が悪くなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.61,0:37:49.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前と同じように体重が減って\N体力がなくなってしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.72,0:37:53.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,医師によると\Nセリアック病ということでした
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.32,0:37:57.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,食事療法によって\N徐々に良くなっていきました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.16,0:38:00.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,2014年まで法律事務所で働きました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.93,0:38:04.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫も退職したので\N別の場所に引っ越しました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.57,0:38:08.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,今はベテル･コンサルタント\Nとして奉仕しています
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.30,0:38:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世に仕える人は文字通り奴隷です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.07,0:38:16.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバに奴隷として仕える人は\N実際には自由です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.41,0:38:19.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えるなら幸せになれます
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.51,0:38:23.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に働けるなんて最高です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.75,0:38:26.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを本当に身近に感じるためには
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.79,0:38:30.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのために一歩\N踏み出す必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.83,0:38:33.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに一生懸命仕えることで
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.46,0:38:36.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい人生を送ってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.36,0:38:40.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかのどんな生き方とも\N比べものになりません
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.21,0:38:51.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹が頑張ってこれたのはなぜですか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.35,0:38:55.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つには めげない心を\N持っていたからです
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.25,0:39:01.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすれば私たちも\Nめげない心を持てますか
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.92,0:39:04.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つの役立つ点を
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.26,0:39:10.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ガイユス･グロッケンティン兄弟が\N 朝の崇拝で話してくださいました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.30,0:39:15.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリアはイエスが話すのを\Nずっと聞いていました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.77,0:39:17.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,立派です
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.84,0:39:20.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい優先順位を持っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.34,0:39:22.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い手本です
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.58,0:39:24.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも姉妹のマルタは
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.75,0:39:29.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,コメント文にある通り\Nイエスから愛ある助言を受けました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.95,0:39:34.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日は少し マルタの身になって\N考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.72,0:39:38.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスがユダヤの大変な地域で\N宣教を行っていた間
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.06,0:39:41.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,マルタはイエスを家に泊めて
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.66,0:39:44.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,一生懸命にサポートしました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.33,0:39:47.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,今回イエスが家に来る前
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.80,0:39:52.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリアとマルタは恐らく一緒に\N準備をしていたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.57,0:39:57.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもイエスが来ると マリアは\N手伝うのをやめてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.61,0:40:00.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,マルタはどう感じたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.85,0:40:04.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分一人で準備しなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.49,0:40:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐らくマルタは心穏やかでは\Nいられなかったことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.12,0:40:13.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,いらいらしてきたに違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.26,0:40:17.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹のマリアはイエスのもとから\N離れようとしません
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.50,0:40:20.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでマルタはイエスに
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.57,0:40:24.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリアに「手伝うよう\N言ってください」と頼みます
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.64,0:40:30.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも驚いたことに 自分がイエスから\N助言を受けてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.54,0:40:33.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなただったらどう感じますか
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.25,0:40:35.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,善かれと思ってしているのに
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.48,0:40:39.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,褒め言葉ではなく\N助言を受けてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.42,0:40:43.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,目には涙があふれるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.99,0:40:46.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,ショックのあまり
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.19,0:40:49.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,胸が苦しくなるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.26,0:40:53.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,マルタはイエスに\Nこう言いたくなったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.90,0:40:58.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ひどいです！あなたのために\N頑張っているのに 助言ですか
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.61,0:41:01.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,じゃあこれからは私も話を聞きます
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.11,0:41:05.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも食事は誰が準備して\Nくださるんでしょうね」
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.68,0:41:10.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろんマルタが何を考え
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.08,0:41:12.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう言ったかは分かりません
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.95,0:41:16.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも分かっているのは\Nコメント文にある通り
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.46,0:41:20.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,マルタがイエスの愛ある助言を\N銘記したということです
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.73,0:41:23.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,では つらい気持ちを克服し\N前に進むために
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.90,0:41:26.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が助けになりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.70,0:41:31.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく言われるのは\N「めげない心」を持つことです
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.57,0:41:33.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,めげない心を持つ人は
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.64,0:41:37.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,うれしくないことや\N傷つくようなことがあっても
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.38,0:41:39.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに立ち直れます
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.65,0:41:43.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょうど このばねのような\N力があります
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.32,0:41:46.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,プレッシャーがあってもそれに耐え
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.35,0:41:49.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,元の形に戻ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.32,0:41:53.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではどうすればめげない心を持つ人
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.76,0:41:56.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに諦めない人になれますか
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.46,0:41:59.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つの点を考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.93,0:42:05.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず1つ目は 事実を直視することです
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.14,0:42:07.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,事実を直視する
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.41,0:42:10.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 28章を開いてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.88,0:42:15.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい状況の時にはこう自問すべきです
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.82,0:42:18.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分の状況を本当に理解し
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.52,0:42:21.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,受け入れているだろうか」
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.16,0:42:25.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 28:26にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.06,0:42:27.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,前半に注目してください
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.36,0:42:34.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分に頼る人は愚かであ［る］」
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.64,0:42:38.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちには 見たくない\Nものから目を背け
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.64,0:42:41.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,見たいものだけを見る傾向があります
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.21,0:42:46.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かがあるとすぐに\N自分のせいではない と考えがちです
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.21,0:42:50.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 先ほどの聖句の\N後半にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.65,0:42:56.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,「知恵によって歩む人は安全である」
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.49,0:43:01.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 物事をありのままに\N見る必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.66,0:43:04.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,現実を直視します
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.33,0:43:07.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,現実を直視するのは簡単ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.53,0:43:10.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,時には嫌な気持ちになったり
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.10,0:43:13.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,つらい気持ちになったり\Nするかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.01,0:43:16.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒ペテロはそう感じました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.18,0:43:21.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスを3度否定し イエスから\N見つめられた時のことです
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.42,0:43:24.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもペテロは事実を直視し
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.62,0:43:27.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,外に出て泣き崩れました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.02,0:43:31.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,言い訳を探そうとしたりは\Nしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.39,0:43:35.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,この経験によって また他の機会にも\N助言を受けたことで
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.53,0:43:41.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロは進歩し 与えられた仕事を\Nいっそうよく果たせるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.34,0:43:44.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目は何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.64,0:43:48.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ポジティブな見方をすることです
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.84,0:43:51.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人たちは問題にぶつかると
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.51,0:43:54.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,「どうして自分がこんな目に\N遭わなければならないのだろう」と
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.65,0:43:57.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,思うかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.92,0:44:00.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分は犠牲者だと思っているので
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.65,0:44:05.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした状況から何も\N学ぶことができません
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.69,0:44:08.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも私たちは聖書を学んでいるので
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.73,0:44:13.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい問題にぶつかることが\Nあるのはなぜかを知っています
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.83,0:44:17.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,物事の全体を見るなら\Nポジティブな見方ができます
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.87,0:44:21.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,めげない心を持ち うれしくない状況や
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.04,0:44:25.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい状況に置かれても\N頑張り続けることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.18,0:44:28.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけでなく 難しい状況を
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.22,0:44:31.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かを学ぶチャンスと\N見ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.49,0:44:36.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰一人 完全ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.32,0:44:40.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰もが時折 何かのことで失敗します
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.99,0:44:43.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような時にどうするかは
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.23,0:44:45.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち次第です
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.70,0:44:49.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,失敗から学ぶことが大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.04,0:44:53.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,後ろではなく 前に目を向けます
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.14,0:44:56.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,目標を持ちます 新しい目標です
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.94,0:45:00.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,覚えておられると思いますが\Nハロルド･キング兄弟は
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.65,0:45:05.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,独房の中でもめげない態度を示しました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.19,0:45:10.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした状況の中で どのように\Nできることを行ったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.62,0:45:12.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.46,0:45:17.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,「“伝道”活動の\Nプログラムを組みました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.46,0:45:21.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,独房の中でだれに\N伝道するのかですって？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.80,0:45:24.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は 記憶していた事柄をもとに
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.71,0:45:27.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,適切な聖書の話を準備し
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.01,0:45:32.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,頭の中でいろいろな人に\N伝道することにしました」
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.41,0:45:36.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも ポジティブな\N見方を持っていれば
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.72,0:45:38.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい問題にぶつかっても
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.92,0:45:42.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,トンネルの先の光を見ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.29,0:45:44.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,その光が見えていれば
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.66,0:45:47.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,頑張り続ける力が得られます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.63,0:45:50.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう耐えられない という気持ちに
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.33,0:45:53.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,押しつぶされることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.17,0:45:56.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目は 自分について
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.87,0:46:00.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,バランスの取れた見方を持つことです
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.87,0:46:03.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初に考えた通り 事実を直視すると
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.01,0:46:07.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,つらい気持ちになったり\Nがっかりしたりすることがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.68,0:46:09.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもめげない心を持つ人は
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.82,0:46:12.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,失敗したり間違いを犯したりしても
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.92,0:46:16.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分に価値がないとは考えません
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.19,0:46:19.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 7章を開いてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.53,0:46:22.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロの手本から\N学ぶことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.63,0:46:25.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロはどんな見方を\Nしていたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.90,0:46:30.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは時折 自分の弱点のために\N気落ちしました
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.87,0:46:35.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,7章を読むと パウロは自分が\N罪に束縛されていたために
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.94,0:46:39.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,良心の痛みを感じていた\Nことが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.75,0:46:43.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,24節をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.45,0:46:45.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロはこう述べています
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.89,0:46:49.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は実に惨めな人間です！」
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.36,0:46:53.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは不完全でした
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.76,0:46:55.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもだからといって
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.80,0:46:59.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分に価値がないとは考えませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.43,0:47:02.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは9年後 親しい友テモテに
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.84,0:47:05.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,2通目の手紙を書きました
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.14,0:47:07.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,死ぬ少し前のことです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.17,0:47:10.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の人生を振り返ってこう言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.41,0:47:14.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,テモテ第二 4:7です
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.18,0:47:16.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.62,0:47:21.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は立派に戦いました
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.52,0:47:26.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,競走を最後まで走りました
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.26,0:47:31.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,クリスチャンの信条を守りました」
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.27,0:47:34.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロの問題や内面の葛藤が
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.90,0:47:37.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,奇跡的になくなることは\Nありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.60,0:47:40.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもパウロは諦めることなく
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.11,0:47:43.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの奉仕を一生懸命に行いました
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.08,0:47:49.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 次のようなネガティブな言葉\Nで自分を責めないようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.85,0:47:54.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分は駄目だ」\N「自分には価値がない」
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.35,0:47:57.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の生活のポジティブな面に目を向け
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.36,0:47:59.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の長所について考えるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.86,0:48:04.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分についてバランスの取れた\N見方を保てるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.87,0:48:06.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,まとめです
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.90,0:48:10.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,マルタの例から めげない心を育て
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.27,0:48:13.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,保つことの大切さを学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.24,0:48:15.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つの方法があります
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.61,0:48:18.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,事実を直視すること
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.65,0:48:20.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,ポジティブな見方をすること
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.01,0:48:25.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分についてバランスの取れた\N見方を保つことです
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.39,0:48:30.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書には パラダイスでの生活が
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.89,0:48:34.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれほど素晴らしいかが描かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.90,0:48:37.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のミュージックビデオを\Nご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.83,0:48:41.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来の素晴らしい生活を思い描くと
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.30,0:48:44.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,幸せな気持ちになります
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.92,0:49:05.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,静かに目を閉じ 心の旅に出よう
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.76,0:49:14.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に扉 開こう
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.60,0:49:27.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,爽やかなそよ風 肩をなでて導く
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.55,0:49:36.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,少し先へ進もう
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.23,0:49:50.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,さあ ほら 幸せな歌声
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.67,0:50:01.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,そっと耳すませば 聞こえる
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.02,0:50:11.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,もういないあの人 \N会えるんだ また必ず
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.32,0:50:20.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずっと一緒にいれる
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.10,0:50:57.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,痛みが消えていく 辛い記憶とともに
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.57,0:51:05.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな 心 躍る
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.98,0:51:20.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,さあ ほら 幸せな歌声
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.73,0:51:31.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,そっと耳すませば 聞こえる
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.11,0:51:41.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の目に見える 将来の約束が
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.78,0:51:53.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,道を照らす 優しく
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.73,0:52:00.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,その日まで そう ずっと
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.63,0:52:10.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバありがとう 今を生きる力
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.44,0:52:21.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,心晴れる 今日も
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.36,0:52:31.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんと美しい歌と映像でしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.10,0:52:33.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のプログラムでは
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.23,0:52:36.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の歴史を振り返りました
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.14,0:52:38.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,思い出に浸るためではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.54,0:52:42.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが約束通りご自分の組織を
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.91,0:52:47.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,絶えず良いものにしてきたことを\N思い返すためです
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.18,0:52:52.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しいシリーズ\N「JWヒストリー」も始まりました
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.65,0:52:55.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,今回は エホバへの崇拝で
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.52,0:52:59.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌うことがどれほど重要かを学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.39,0:53:04.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがご自分に仕える人たちを\Nどのように祝福するかも学びました
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.83,0:53:08.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,バルネーブ姉妹はきらびやかな\N生活を後にし
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.50,0:53:10.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,豊かな祝福を味わってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.97,0:53:14.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミルズ兄弟はいろいろな問題を\N経験してきましたが 
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.91,0:53:17.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは兄弟を支えています
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.24,0:53:22.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は他の人を助けることで\N喜びを保っています
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.52,0:53:24.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,お別れする前に
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.05,0:53:29.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹からの\Nビデオレターを楽しみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.92,0:53:35.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月はエクアドルの\N兄弟姉妹たちを訪ねます
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.70,0:53:38.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エクアドルには赤道という\N意味があります
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.90,0:53:42.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,文字通り 赤道直下にあります
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.44,0:53:46.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エクアドルにはガラパゴス諸島や\Nアンデス山脈があり 
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.01,0:53:50.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,アマゾン川流域も含まれます
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.74,0:53:53.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはチンボラソ山です
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.61,0:53:56.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球は赤道方向に少し膨らんでいるので
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.88,0:54:01.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球の中心からの距離で言えば\N世界一高い山です
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.72,0:54:06.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 100年以上前に造られた\Nアンデスの山岳鉄道です
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.23,0:54:10.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,1946年に最初に到着した\N宣教者たちも
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.56,0:54:12.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,この鉄道を使いました
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.63,0:54:16.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,現在エクアドルでは\N10万人以上のエホバの証人が
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.54,0:54:19.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い知らせを伝えています
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.37,0:54:21.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,2020年の記念式には
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.51,0:54:24.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,30万人近くの人が出席しました
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.64,0:54:27.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,チョンタプンタ･キチュア語会衆は
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.28,0:54:29.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,元は孤立したグループでした
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.38,0:54:31.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹は生計を立てるため
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.62,0:54:35.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,花を育てたり砂金を集めたりしています
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.59,0:54:39.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 一番力を注いでいるのは宣教です
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.43,0:54:43.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,徹底的に伝道するためには\N努力を惜しみません
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.53,0:54:46.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,橋がなければ別の方法で渡ります
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.77,0:54:50.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,2そうのボート\Nエノクとエノク2を使って
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.57,0:54:54.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,キチュア語を話す人たちが\N住む地域に行きます
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.51,0:54:57.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,辺ぴな場所では携帯が\Nつながりにくいですが
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.61,0:55:01.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,この子はそれにめげずに\N電波がよく届く所に行って
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.31,0:55:06.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会に出席したり\N聖書レッスンを受けたりしています
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.52,0:55:08.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,携帯が使えない所では
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.66,0:55:13.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,無線機を使って再訪問や\N聖書レッスンをしています
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.09,0:55:20.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,現地語の1つであるワオラニ語でも\N講演や記念式の話が行われています
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.23,0:55:22.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,この言語の文書はまだありません
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.80,0:55:26.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族と一緒に会衆で\N奉仕しているこの女の子は
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.47,0:55:30.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ワオラニ語を話す子供たちに\Nビデオを見せています
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.34,0:55:32.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ4歳です
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.31,0:55:36.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エクアドルの\Nチョンタプンタ･キチュア語会衆の
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.58,0:55:38.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛する兄弟姉妹が
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.79,0:55:43.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中の仲間に\N愛とあいさつを送っています
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.46,0:55:48.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィーバー兄弟 本当に\Nありがとうございました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.96,0:55:53.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒にプログラムを扱ってくださって\Nとても助かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.37,0:55:59.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち2人から 皆さんに温かい\Nクリスチャン愛を送ります
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.11,0:56:01.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の世界本部から
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.01,0:56:06.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcastingでした
